					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Since we're getting picky about it, all that really exist are 28 6-bit palette entries, which the $3F00-$3FFF region is mapped to. In binary, the entries are mapped to the following combinations of the low 8 bits of the address (X = don't care):
<br />xxxx0000
<br />xxxx0100
<br />xxxx1000
<br />xxxx1100
<br />xxx00001
<br />xxx00010
<br />xxx00011
<br />xxx00101
<br />xxx00110
<br />xxx00111
<br />xxx01001
<br />xxx01010
<br />xxx01011
<br />xxx01101
<br />xxx01110
<br />xxx01111
<br />xxx10001
<br />xxx10010
<br />xxx10011
<br />xxx10101
<br />xxx10110
<br />xxx10111
<br />xxx11001
<br />xxx11010
<br />xxx11011
<br />xxx11101
<br />xxx11110
<br />xxx11111</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

